<div id="review_314157986" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/314157986" />
    <a title="Karlyne Landrum" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2158408-karlyne-landrum"><img alt="Karlyne Landrum" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1270093598p2/2158408.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/314157986?book_show_action=true">Apr 17, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Karlyne Landrum" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Karlyne Landrum" href="/user/show/2158408-karlyne-landrum">Karlyne Landrum</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer314157986" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2024563054897952784">This is not my usual genre; although I sometimes like Young Adult fiction, I don&apos;t tend to seek it out. And I don&apos;t like scary books, either! So, when a friend insisted that I read it, I was a bit leery. But I have to say I thoroughly enjoyed it. Some of the imagery is gorgeous; I love the picture of the characters laid out on the side of the riverbank in their nightclothes and I could feel the sunshiny wind on my own arm when Sonnet drove her best friend&apos;s car without &quot;permission&quot;. The plot, to</span>
  <span id="freeText2024563054897952784" style="display:none">This is not my usual genre; although I sometimes like Young Adult fiction, I don't tend to seek it out. And I don't like scary books, either! So, when a friend insisted that I read it, I was a bit leery. But I have to say I thoroughly enjoyed it. Some of the imagery is gorgeous; I love the picture of the characters laid out on the side of the riverbank in their nightclothes and I could feel the sunshiny wind on my own arm when Sonnet drove her best friend's car without "permission". The plot, too, is fresh. Time travelling is not a new idea, but the idea that people can travel willy-nilly, forward and backward, without having a say in where or when is a new one to me. However, the reason I give this such a high rating is that the characters have stayed with me for several weeks. They're not all perfectly drawn (I would like to have known more of Emme!), but they are real in their youth and foibles, and because of that I highly recommend it. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2024563054897952784" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


