<div id="review_538223082" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/538223082" />
    <a title="liirogue" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/334806-liirogue"><img alt="liirogue" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1191105513p2/334806.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/538223082?book_show_action=true">Feb 16, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="liirogue" class="user" itemprop="url" name="liirogue" href="/user/show/334806-liirogue">liirogue</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer538223082" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3180260648058382978">I am rereading this before reading the sequel, and I&apos;m glad I did. I had forgotten just how much I enjoyed this. It&apos;s a time travel novel, but quite different than most in the genre. The characters in this novel are known as the Lost - they travel randomly through time. They have no control over it and never know where (or when) they&apos;ll wake up. They form rag-tag families as various individuals join or leave the little group, but once you are separated from the group you will probably never be r</span>
  <span id="freeText3180260648058382978" style="display:none">I am rereading this before reading the sequel, and I'm glad I did. I had forgotten just how much I enjoyed this. It's a time travel novel, but quite different than most in the genre. The characters in this novel are known as the Lost - they travel randomly through time. They have no control over it and never know where (or when) they'll wake up. They form rag-tag families as various individuals join or leave the little group, but once you are separated from the group you will probably never be reunited. I found it fascinating and heart rending at the same time. Just how close could you get to someone knowing they could disappear any day? And how would your priorities change if you were truly living just to get by? You can work hard to buy nice things and live comfortably, but why? You'll just leave it all behind and have to start all over again.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3180260648058382978" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


